About
Ibn Battuta Mall blends shopping, dining and entertainment with history, culture and the story of a remarkable explorer. It is the largest themed shopping mall in Dubai and one of the city’s most exciting shopping and retail destinations.
Duration: More than 3 hours

    Loved this Themed Mall
    Amazing mall. It's huge, loved the different themed sections. Great food options along with great shopping. We were staying next door in the Avani hotel so visiting the mall was so convenient. Spent 2 days trying to see it all & visit as many shops that were pertinent to us. Bought men's & women's clothes (great to find big sizes) jewellery along with supplies from the Carrefours supermarket. Lovely cafes n 2 big food halls. There is a train station adjacent. Have previously been to The Dubai Mall & the Mall of the Emirates & while perhaps not as big it was still a great mall
    Visited October 2023
    Traveled as a couple

Great mall
Oct 2024 • Family
This was the first place we visited when we arrived and luckily, as we were staying in the Oaks Ibn Battuta Hotel, it was a mere stones throw away.
At first it looks small and fairly empty but as you walk around you realise it just continues to go on and on with some fantastic shops.
The carrefour is wonderful as expected and it’s a much more sedate and quiet mall compared to some of the others.
I’d highly recommend a visit!
